			<blockquote>
			<font face=helvetica size=-1>
<font face=helvetica size=3><b>Tuesday October 31, 2000</b></font>
			<hr align=LEFT size=1 width=500 color=#000080>
<!---------------news---------------->
<Br>
<font face=helvetica size=2 color=#000080><b>Speaking of Half-Life. . .</b> - 12:16:55</font>
<br><br><blockquote>
Autolycus at <b><a href=http://halflife.gamedesign.net/>HL/ERC</a></b> goes over the gl_wireframe command that appeared in HL 1.1.0.4. It sounds a bit like Quake 2/3 'showtris'...<blockquote>gl_wireframe...allows you to view polygons in your level as they were actually split up by the tools. This lets you see what areas of your level need optimizing.<p>set gl_wireframe to 2 to enable the entire PVS (potentially visible set) to be outlined.  This will show you exactly what the engine sees and how it is broken into polygons.</blockquote>This console command, combined with <a href=http://halflife.gamedesign.net/resources/zhlt.shtml>Zoner's Half-Life Tools</a>, should make life MUCH easier when optimizing Half-Life maps for best playability.
<b><p align=right>Update by <a href="mailto:monsto@gamedesign.net">Monsto</a></p></b>
</blockquote>
<h3>Go <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net">back</a> to the main news page...</h3>
			</font>
